Let me know! Thanks!
@percyliang

@csinchok @kand 
This fixes issue where pinned content bubbling caused a query_raw() to be used, which then caused all subsequent query() calls to be ignored. 

As noted in the comments, this is a workaround for ElasticUtils limitations, which is deprecated anyway and should be replaced.

Modified the installation of numpy for appveyor and travis to 1.9.2.  Also added a requirements.txt file that can be read by nupic so they have the same version of numpy.

@rhyolight

For numenta.nupic/#1516

@tseaver I discovered this while outfitting the Pub/Sub system tests to run with the emulator. When using an un-authorized client [like in `datastore`][1], it caused an error in `httplib2`. We have never experience this because `oauth2client` has [bailed us out][2] until this point.

[1]: https://github.com/GoogleCloudPlatform/gcloud-python/blob/ffe5869aa7c31bd82483e4d52adacbf83cf0fd69/system_tests/datastore.py#L75
[2]: https://github.com/google/oauth2client/blob/8f8df1f5977ec76d50cb3dca9a31044cfd1fb9b4/oauth2client/client.py#L464-L465

1. Redefine the properties;
2. Introduce concept of command scope. The errors happen during a
command scope are associated with the command

So I can override the validate method in the view like this:

```python
from oscarapi.views.basket import AddProductView as _AddProductView

class AddProductView(_AddProductView):
    def validate(self, basket, product, quantity):
        # check if there is a orderlimit for this product
        allowed, message = basket.add_product_allowed(product, quantity)
        if not allowed:
            return False, message
        return super(
            AddProductView, self).validate(basket, product, quantity)
```

- Docstrings;
- "Fix" some line breaks;
- Removed one unused variable from `do_respawn_auto_scaling_group`

2 warnings remain do the 2 TODOs.

- Added PIE linker flags (when compiled in terminal as in the tutorial, file couldn't run because  of "Only position independent executables (PIE) are supported" error);
- Fixed local reference issue in the example code for the tutorial;
- In the .md files:  -DBUILD_SHARED_LIBS=false solves "librealsense2.so not found" error.
